May 24 2005	The maybe shuttle	So, we could save some money by staying out near the airport at the Howard Johnsons ... it was sure to be a bit ... um ... cheapish. But we could handle that since we would only be sleeping there anyway but ... how would we deal with the coming and going when we want to go to the Strip or Downtown? OH, no problem ... the people on the phone said that they have a free shuttle out at the Howard Johnsons that takes you to the Strip or to the Airport. They said that it runs regularly throughout the day. Perfect! We booked the room and went on vacation to Vegas. It took a while and from the airport it was necessary to call them and wait but hey ... it isn't far. Actually, I have no complaints about the shuttle service to and from the airport. They only have one van but they will interrupt other plans to do an airport run for any of the guests at the two hotels that that shuttle serves (especially the crews of one of the airlines who all stay at the other hotel).And there's the rub. They tell you that the shuttle will drive you to the Tropicana Hotel on the Strip every hour on the hour and they will pick you up from the Tropicana soon after the hour (the exact time depending on traffic). Fair enough ... it's only one spot on the Strip instead of what I had assumed when I left home but still, they get you to the Strip as advertised. But wait! There is only one van and they serve two hotels and ANY call to the airport will cause them to suspend the scheduled run to the the Tropicana. So, there you are at the Tropicana waiting for your ride to the hotel so you can catch some sleep but ... the van doesn't come and it doesn't come and ... it doesn't come (hours sometimes). You use your cell phone to call and there is always and only one response from the hotel and it is probably true -- they are doing a run to the airport. In fact, it is not unreasonable to think that they are doing six or seven different runs to and from the airport before they next get a chance to go back to the Tropicana run. And when they do come ...there are 25 people waiting for that van that seats 12 so you'll have to wait till the next run but there may be airport runs between now and the return. Time to go find a taxi (don't try calling one in Vegas, they take a very long time ... go to one of the bigger hotels where the taxis come to line up to take riders. It'll cost maybe $7 to get back to your cheap hotel out by the airport. Don't you wish that you called that $7 taxi before you waited for 2 hours and THEN called?I hope your plan was not to just run back to the hotel to change clothes and go out again ... because the shuttle is doing an airport run ... or two. Have a nice weekend.	
