Apr 30 2005	good bargain for price	I read others reviews after I made my reservation and was a bit scared, but realized that for $30.00 I was going to get a place to sleep. I arrived early but was not allowed to check in till 3pm. The King/Smoking room I reserved never became available so I took a double. Rooms are small, but overall was clean. One towel rack was busted and lying in the bathroom. There were no towels or alarm clock and it took three requests to get them. I used the pool which was pleasant and spent some time playing the poker machines with $1 taps of beer. My wake up call came on time and I had a quiet nites sleep (Sunday). The free airport shuttle had me there in 5 minutes. The main reason I stayed here was to be close to the airport and needed a free shuttle to cut costs. Overall, for 30.00 bucks it was a bargain and I would stay again in the same situation. People need to realize that for 30.00 bucks your not going to get the things you do for 50.00, 80.00 or more. Budget Travel Magazine take note.	
